
<h1>Welcome to Hogwarts, <%= @wizard.name %>!</h1>
<p>Congratulations on your acceptance. Your Hogwarts house is <strong><%= @wizard.hogwarts_house %></strong>.</p>

<h2>Hogwarts School Instructions for New Students</h2>
<ul>
	<li><strong>Term Start:</strong> The school year begins on September 1st. Students travel to Hogwarts via the Hogwarts Express from Platform 9¾ at King's Cross Station.</li>
	<li><strong>Sorting Ceremony:</strong> Upon arrival, you will be sorted into one of four houses: Gryffindor, Hufflepuff, Ravenclaw, or Slytherin. Your house will be your family at Hogwarts.</li>
	<li><strong>Uniform:</strong> All students must wear the official Hogwarts uniform during lessons and meals in the Great Hall.</li>
	<li><strong>Classes:</strong> Core subjects include Transfiguration, Charms, Potions, Defence Against the Dark Arts, Herbology, History of Magic, Astronomy, and Flying (for first years).</li>
	<li><strong>Common Rooms:</strong> After the Start-of-Term Feast, you will be led to your house common room by a prefect. Only house members may enter their own common room.</li>
	<li><strong>Daily Routine:</strong> Breakfast is served at 7:30 a.m. Classes begin at 9 a.m. Dinner is served in the evening, followed by study and social time in your common room.</li>
	<li><strong>Rules:</strong> Magic is not permitted in the corridors. Thievery and rule-breaking are not tolerated. The Forbidden Forest and certain areas (such as the third-floor corridor) are out of bounds unless permitted by staff.</li>
	<li><strong>Examinations:</strong> End-of-year exams are held in June. Fifth years take O.W.L.s, and seventh years take N.E.W.T.s.</li>
	<li><strong>Holidays:</strong> Students may go home for Christmas and Easter, or stay at Hogwarts and enjoy special feasts and activities.</li>
	<li><strong>Extra-curriculars:</strong> Join clubs, play Quidditch, and participate in magical events throughout the year!</li>
</ul>
<p>
Remember the school motto: <em>Draco Dormiens Nunquam Titillandus</em> (“Never tickle a sleeping dragon”).
We wish you a magical and successful year at Hogwarts!
</p>
<hr>
<p>
If you have any questions, please ask your Head of House or a prefect. Welcome to the finest school of witchcraft and wizardry in the world!
</p>
